<reply id="uk.org.publicwhip/wrans/2006-06-27b.139.2" speakerid="uk.org.publicwhip/lord/100164" speakername="Lord Davies of Oldham" colon=":" colnum="139"  url="http://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/ld199697/ldhansrd/pdvn/lds06/text/60627w01.htm#60627w01_spnew2">
	<p pid="b.139.2/1">The latest firm estimate of the backlog in street lighting is &pound;1.65 billion, as reported to the Transport Select Committee in June 2004.</p>
	<p pid="b.139.2/2">For carriageways, footways and structures, we are actively seeking better information from local authorities and elsewhere. All local highway authorities have been encouraged to produce asset management plans for their roads. These will consist of inventories of stock, its existing condition, and target condition based upon desired service levels. These asset management plans, together with better information on the most effective remedial work and its costs, will allow more accurate estimates to be made of the funding required.</p>
	<p pid="b.139.2/3">The National Road Maintenance Condition Survey for 2005 showed that the interim target of halting carriageway deterioration by 2004 had been well achieved. There has been a significant improvement in road conditions in England since 2000, and the Government consider that they are still on track to meet the target of eliminating local highway maintenance backlogs by 2010&ndash;11.</p>
</reply>
